                    "source": "Enables a non-encrypted (HTTP) server on the port designated below.  By default this plugin requires a secure HTTPS connection, but in safe environments you may turn on the non-encrypted server to simplify interacting with the API. Interactions with the API will still require the API Key shown above.  Under no circumstances is it recommended that you expose this service to the internet, especially if you turn on this feature!",
